The paper deals with distributed computing systems and coded computation, which are typically studied in the sub-category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also utilizes concepts from erasure coding, which falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper proposes a fine-grained model for matrix-vector computation, which involves dealing with sparse matrices, and discusses code designs, which are topics studied in the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper also discusses leveraging partial computations performed by straggler nodes, which is a topic studied in the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
